title: For Sale:  Beretta 96D Police Special
postcontent:
This is a Beretta Model 96D Police Special, chambered in .40 S&W caliber. It was manufactured in the United States in 1997 for the Maryland State Police. It has Trijicon night sights from 1997. The white rings around the tritium vials make excellent 3-dot sights for daylight shooting, but the vials are very dim. Trijicon will install new vials in the sights for a nominal fee. (Visit https://www.trijicon.com/na_en/support/faq_BNTNS.php for more information.) Markings are clear and crisp. The bore is mirror bright with sharp lands & grooves. As with most police trade-ins, it shows signs of carry but few signs of being shot much. See the accompanying picture for condition. Additional high resolution pictures are available on request. The pistol comes with 2 correct factory 11 round magazines marked "RESTRICTED LAW ENFORCEMENT/GOVERNMENT USE ONLY" and "PB CAL.40 S&W - MADE IN ITALY".  In case you are unfamiliar with Beretta D-type pistols, this 96D is a double action only (DAO) pistol with no manual safety. For this reason, some enthusiasts call them "slick slides".

You can view the owner's manual here: stevespages.com/pdf/beretta_96d.pdf

Face to face transaction only.  Buyer must present government picture ID showing you are a resident of Ohio of legal age to purchase this firearm.
